            <title>[GROOVY-3077] Bindable transformation causes verification errors with static properties</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3077</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you add the Bindable transformation to a class with static properties, then a VerifyError will be generated at runtime. In my mildly abused version of the transformation, I added a check for isStatic() to createListenerSetter, and that solved the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
